    <data key="d0">Clickatech Smart Home Solution for Luxury Apartments (Stonehenge NYC)</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3BGPEFFCpvk</data>
    <data key="d2">Clickatech developed an IoT smart home solution for Stonehenge luxury apartments, retrofitting existing units with custom hardware (smart plugs, temperature and humidity sensors) running FreeRTOS. The architecture leverages AWS IoT Core for device connectivity (MQTT, certificate-based auth, Device Shadow, Registry) and routes data to IoT Analytics for aggregated reporting (QuickSight) and Elasticsearch for near real-time fault detection (Kibana). Lambda functions process device metrics into DynamoDB and power custom Alexa skills (Resident and Office) integrated with Alexa for Business. RDS stores building/apartment structural data. Separately, enterprise data from a financial reporting system is backed up to S3 and transformed for Salesforce and Einstein Analytics for investor insights. The system aims to provide voice control, automated maintenance, and property management efficiencies.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
